  "prompt": "Is there a way to see someones likes on instagram?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Instagram does not provide a way to publicly view someone else's likes directly. However, there are a few ways to get an idea of what someone likes or engages with on Instagram:\n\n1. **Visible Interactions**:\n   - If the person has left likes on public posts, you can see their likes by visiting those posts and checking the list of people who have liked them (if the account is public).\n   - Their comments on public posts are also visible if the account is public.\n\n2. **Following Activity**:\n   - If the person follows hashtags or accounts, you can see their interactions with those hashtags or accounts if they are public.\n\n3. **Shared Content**:\n   - If they share posts to their Stories, you can see the content they are engaging with and promoting.\n\n4. **Mutual Followers**:\n   - If you follow the same accounts, you might see their likes or comments on those accounts' posts.\n\n5. **Third-Party Tools**:\n   - Some third-party apps or services claim to track Instagram activity, but using them violates Instagram's terms of service and may compromise privacy and security. Avoid using such tools.\n\n6. **Private Accounts**:\n   - If the person has a private account, you cannot see their likes or interactions unless you are approved to follow them.\n\nAlways respect others' privacy and use Instagram in accordance with its community guidelines and terms of service.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
